title: I Confronted My Catâ€™s Online Haters & This Is What Happened
description: Apparently my cat has haters. I know. It sounds ridiculous. But every time I post a video of Chip, people assume something terrible happened to his tail. Some report the video. Some leave comments calling him abused. Some even say he needs to be rescued.  This video is the full story of what actually happened and what went down when I finally confronted the people who were spreading misinformation about him. Chip is a Manx cat which means he was born without a tail. There is no injury. No harm. Just genetics and one very confident cat who has no idea there is a debate about him online.  In this video I talk about why Manx cats look the way they do, what the tailless gene is, why his videos get reported, and how the internet reacted when people stepped up to defend him. If you have ever seen a tailless cat or wondered why some cats are born without tails, this will answer everything.  Thank you to everyone who continues to support Chip and helps correct the misinformation. You make a huge difference and Chip would thank you himself if he could stop stealing my snacks long enough to speak.

title: Cats and TIC TAC TOE

title: I Confronted My Catâ€™s Online Haters & This Is What Happened
description: Apparently my cat has haters. I know. It sounds ridiculous. But every time I post a video of Chip, people assume something terrible happened to his tail. Some report the video. Some leave comments calling him abused. Some even say he needs to be rescued.  This video is the full story of what actually happened and what went down when I finally confronted the people who were spreading misinformation about him. Chip is a Manx cat which means he was born without a tail. There is no injury. No harm. Just genetics and one very confident cat who has no idea there is a debate about him online.  In this video I talk about why Manx cats look the way they do, what the tailless gene is, why his videos get reported, and how the internet reacted when people stepped up to defend him. If you have ever seen a tailless cat or wondered why some cats are born without tails, this will answer everything.  Thank you to everyone who continues to support Chip and helps correct the misinformation. You make a huge difference and Chip would thank you himself if he could stop stealing my snacks long enough to speak.

title: Prison Break. The real story
description: A little kitty tries to make her first escape in her life. But she is disturbed by the guard who controls the territory. There are no impossible tasks for the kitty, she tries to do it...  The house is large, but the kitten is still very small. At night, without our supervision, she can go into many dangerous places and fall from a great height. Plus, it is unknown how the kitten and the cat will interact with each other at night. That is why we play it safe and leave the kitten separately at night and put a net around for her own good. title: 2 Cute Kittens Meet for the First Time ğŸ’œ

title: Scared Abandoned Kitten Rescue - Cat Man Chris
description: Weâ€™ll never know the full story of where this little lady came from, but weâ€™re pretty certain she was a RTF kitten here in Tampa, where they are released in the area that they were trapped in before going to the county shelter.  Rules vary across the country, you can learn more here: https://humanepro.org/return-to-field  I believe Return To Field makes sense for adult truly feral cats that were already surviving outside, they can be spayed/neutered/vaccinated and returned, but kittens that are only 2+ months old and are just scared out of their mind in a noisy shelter setting being deemed â€œferalâ€â€¦ we are truly failing them, what do YOU think?  ğŸ± Find me here...  â€¢ https://www.facebook.com/CatManChrisPoole â€¢ https://www.instagram.com/catmanchrispoole â€¢ https://www.tiktok.com/@catmanchrispoole  #KittenRescue #CatManChris #ScaredKitten

title: I Confronted My Catâ€™s Online Haters & This Is What Happened
description: Apparently my cat has haters. I know. It sounds ridiculous. But every time I post a video of Chip, people assume something terrible happened to his tail. Some report the video. Some leave comments calling him abused. Some even say he needs to be rescued.  This video is the full story of what actually happened and what went down when I finally confronted the people who were spreading misinformation about him. Chip is a Manx cat which means he was born without a tail. There is no injury. No harm. Just genetics and one very confident cat who has no idea there is a debate about him online.  In this video I talk about why Manx cats look the way they do, what the tailless gene is, why his videos get reported, and how the internet reacted when people stepped up to defend him. If you have ever seen a tailless cat or wondered why some cats are born without tails, this will answer everything.  Thank you to everyone who continues to support Chip and helps correct the misinformation. You make a huge difference and Chip would thank you himself if he could stop stealing my snacks long enough to speak.

title: When Misty returned to her area, she awaited our visit the next day.
description: #cat #kitten #feedingstreetcats #catrescue   When we returned Misty to her old territory, she began meowing. After we opened the carrier, she came out in amazement, trying to remember the area after more than five months of absence. We gave her food and water and left. But the next morning, we were excited to meet her, only to find her equally excited to visit and cuddle with us, performing some beautiful dance routines. Now, Misty will live a different life than she used to after being spayed. She'll meet new friends, some of whom she already knows. Despite her jealous nature, we'll visit her every day, just as we always have, so she can take her food and love. Misty will miss our shelter, but we won't make her miss us with our frequent visits. Thank you to everyone who helped change her life #cats #kittens #feedingstraycats

title: Kitten drags her dead leg, thanks me in her new room after being rescued
description: #cat #kittenrescue #feedingstreetcats  Hello FSCats Family, One day, I went with my wife to visit the cat family, Alexander and Bransis, to feed them. During the visit, my wife noticed a small kitten hiding in a corner, seeming frightened and alone. When we tried to approach her, we discovered that her hind leg was swollen with an old injury.  After an examination at the veterinary clinic, the doctor informed us that the injury was severe and might require amputation in the future. The vet provided her with a painkiller and treated the swelling. We then brought the kitten to our private shelter, where she began acclimating to her new room, moving with difficulty while dragging her injured leg.  After eating ravenously, she approached me and meowed softly as if thanking us. I prepared a warm bed for her, treated her old wound, and gently cleaned her ears. Now, the kitten lives in a safe place under the care of our team, who work tirelessly for her comfort and treatment. We have become her new family, providing her with love and protection from the dangers of the street. I urge all members of the FSCats family to extend their support and open their hearts to these creatures who need care from all of us. #kittens #catrescue #feedingstraycats

title: After Queen the cat was spayed she gave me a sweet thank you.
description: #cat #kitten #feedingstreetcats   We arrived at the veterinary clinic after a twenty-five-minute journey. As soon as I opened the carrier door, Queen, the queen cat, emerged, looking around trying to comprehend the new place she had arrived at. She began sniffing the table she was placed on with curiosity, as if she were wondering to herself: "Has my refuge changed since I was placed in the car?"  After an hour and a half, Queen had undergone the surgical procedure and had gradually begun regaining consciousness from the effects of the anesthesia. Her gait was unsteady and unstable, as she was still under the influence of the medication. I tried to reassure her with gentle words and placed a bowl with a little water near her, but I refrained from offering food because that could expose her to the risk of choking before she had fully recovered.  The next day, Queen had fully awakened from the effects of the anesthesia and seemed full of vitality when she greeted me. She was eager to get her favorite food, but she first had to take a dose of antibiotic medicine. And after she finished the medicine, it was time for the food she had been so patiently waiting for.  As soon as she finished her meal, she came to me and expressed her gratitude in an exceedingly gentle manner, then headed to a quiet corner in her temporary room to relax. After two or three days, Queen will finally return to join her cat friends, after completing the necessary recovery period in temporary isolation.  #kittens #cats #feedingstraycats

The names in the litter are based on famous composers: * Antonio Vivaldi: Spring * Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart: Eine Kleine Nachtmusik * Ludwig van Beethoven: FÃ¼r Elise * Richard Strauss: Also Sprach Zarathustra * Clara Schumann: Piano Concerto * Edvard Grieg: Morning Mood * Johann Sebastian Bach: C Major Preulude  For more videos with my Maine Coons, take a look at my other channel:  https://www.youtube.com/@Maine_Coon_Adventures  The kittens have released their own merch collection! title: Scared Abandoned Kitten Rescue - Cat Man Chris
description: Weâ€™ll never know the full story of where this little lady came from, but weâ€™re pretty certain she was a RTF kitten here in Tampa, where they are released in the area that they were trapped in before going to the county shelter.  Rules vary across the country, you can learn more here: https://humanepro.org/return-to-field  I believe Return To Field makes sense for adult truly feral cats that were already surviving outside, they can be spayed/neutered/vaccinated and returned, but kittens that are only 2+ months old and are just scared out of their mind in a noisy shelter setting being deemed â€œferalâ€â€¦ we are truly failing them, what do YOU think?  ğŸ± Find me here...  â€¢ https://www.facebook.com/CatManChrisPoole â€¢ https://www.instagram.com/catmanchrispoole â€¢ https://www.tiktok.com/@catmanchrispoole  #KittenRescue #CatManChris #ScaredKitten

title: When Misty returned to her area, she awaited our visit the next day.
description: #cat #kitten #feedingstreetcats #catrescue   When we returned Misty to her old territory, she began meowing. After we opened the carrier, she came out in amazement, trying to remember the area after more than five months of absence. We gave her food and water and left. But the next morning, we were excited to meet her, only to find her equally excited to visit and cuddle with us, performing some beautiful dance routines. Now, Misty will live a different life than she used to after being spayed. She'll meet new friends, some of whom she already knows. Despite her jealous nature, we'll visit her every day, just as we always have, so she can take her food and love. Misty will miss our shelter, but we won't make her miss us with our frequent visits. Thank you to everyone who helped change her life #cats #kittens #feedingstraycats

title: Kitten drags her dead leg, thanks me in her new room after being rescued
description: #cat #kittenrescue #feedingstreetcats  Hello FSCats Family, One day, I went with my wife to visit the cat family, Alexander and Bransis, to feed them. During the visit, my wife noticed a small kitten hiding in a corner, seeming frightened and alone. When we tried to approach her, we discovered that her hind leg was swollen with an old injury.  After an examination at the veterinary clinic, the doctor informed us that the injury was severe and might require amputation in the future. The vet provided her with a painkiller and treated the swelling. We then brought the kitten to our private shelter, where she began acclimating to her new room, moving with difficulty while dragging her injured leg.  After eating ravenously, she approached me and meowed softly as if thanking us. I prepared a warm bed for her, treated her old wound, and gently cleaned her ears. Now, the kitten lives in a safe place under the care of our team, who work tirelessly for her comfort and treatment. We have become her new family, providing her with love and protection from the dangers of the street. I urge all members of the FSCats family to extend their support and open their hearts to these creatures who need care from all of us. #kittens #catrescue #feedingstraycats

title: After Queen the cat was spayed she gave me a sweet thank you.
description: #cat #kitten #feedingstreetcats   We arrived at the veterinary clinic after a twenty-five-minute journey. As soon as I opened the carrier door, Queen, the queen cat, emerged, looking around trying to comprehend the new place she had arrived at. She began sniffing the table she was placed on with curiosity, as if she were wondering to herself: "Has my refuge changed since I was placed in the car?"  After an hour and a half, Queen had undergone the surgical procedure and had gradually begun regaining consciousness from the effects of the anesthesia. Her gait was unsteady and unstable, as she was still under the influence of the medication. I tried to reassure her with gentle words and placed a bowl with a little water near her, but I refrained from offering food because that could expose her to the risk of choking before she had fully recovered.  The next day, Queen had fully awakened from the effects of the anesthesia and seemed full of vitality when she greeted me. She was eager to get her favorite food, but she first had to take a dose of antibiotic medicine. And after she finished the medicine, it was time for the food she had been so patiently waiting for.  As soon as she finished her meal, she came to me and expressed her gratitude in an exceedingly gentle manner, then headed to a quiet corner in her temporary room to relax. After two or three days, Queen will finally return to join her cat friends, after completing the necessary recovery period in temporary isolation.  #kittens #cats #feedingstraycats

title: Maine Coon Kittens Growing Up | Day 1 - 100!
description: This is the story of how Freya's Maine Coon kittens Antonio, Richard, Ludwig, Amadeus, Sebastian, Edvard and Clara grow up, from newborn to 100 days old! Follow them as they take their first steps, have their first taste of food, meet their relatives for the first time and learn everything else they need to know to be good cats. At the end, you will also get too see what their lives look like in their new homes! title: Scared Abandoned Kitten Rescue - Cat Man Chris
description: Weâ€™ll never know the full story of where this little lady came from, but weâ€™re pretty certain she was a RTF kitten here in Tampa, where they are released in the area that they were trapped in before going to the county shelter. title: When Misty returned to her area, she awaited our visit the next day.
description: #cat #kitten #feedingstreetcats #catrescue   When we returned Misty to her old territory, she began meowing. After we opened the carrier, she came out in amazement, trying to remember the area after more than five months of absence. We gave her food and water and left. But the next morning, we were excited to meet her, only to find her equally excited to visit and cuddle with us, performing some beautiful dance routines. Now, Misty will live a different life than she used to after being spayed. She'll meet new friends, some of whom she already knows. Despite her jealous nature, we'll visit her every day, just as we always have, so she can take her food and love. Misty will miss our shelter, but we won't make her miss us with our frequent visits. Thank you to everyone who helped change her life #cats #kittens #feedingstraycats

title: Kitten drags her dead leg, thanks me in her new room after being rescued
description: #cat #kittenrescue #feedingstreetcats  Hello FSCats Family, One day, I went with my wife to visit the cat family, Alexander and Bransis, to feed them. During the visit, my wife noticed a small kitten hiding in a corner, seeming frightened and alone. When we tried to approach her, we discovered that her hind leg was swollen with an old injury.  After an examination at the veterinary clinic, the doctor informed us that the injury was severe and might require amputation in the future. The vet provided her with a painkiller and treated the swelling. We then brought the kitten to our private shelter, where she began acclimating to her new room, moving with difficulty while dragging her injured leg.  After eating ravenously, she approached me and meowed softly as if thanking us. I prepared a warm bed for her, treated her old wound, and gently cleaned her ears. Now, the kitten lives in a safe place under the care of our team, who work tirelessly for her comfort and treatment. We have become her new family, providing her with love and protection from the dangers of the street. I urge all members of the FSCats family to extend their support and open their hearts to these creatures who need care from all of us. #kittens #catrescue #feedingstraycats

title: After Queen the cat was spayed she gave me a sweet thank you.
description: #cat #kitten #feedingstreetcats   We arrived at the veterinary clinic after a twenty-five-minute journey. As soon as I opened the carrier door, Queen, the queen cat, emerged, looking around trying to comprehend the new place she had arrived at. She began sniffing the table she was placed on with curiosity, as if she were wondering to herself: "Has my refuge changed since I was placed in the car?"  After an hour and a half, Queen had undergone the surgical procedure and had gradually begun regaining consciousness from the effects of the anesthesia. Her gait was unsteady and unstable, as she was still under the influence of the medication. I tried to reassure her with gentle words and placed a bowl with a little water near her, but I refrained from offering food because that could expose her to the risk of choking before she had fully recovered.  The next day, Queen had fully awakened from the effects of the anesthesia and seemed full of vitality when she greeted me. She was eager to get her favorite food, but she first had to take a dose of antibiotic medicine. And after she finished the medicine, it was time for the food she had been so patiently waiting for.  As soon as she finished her meal, she came to me and expressed her gratitude in an exceedingly gentle manner, then headed to a quiet corner in her temporary room to relax. After two or three days, Queen will finally return to join her cat friends, after completing the necessary recovery period in temporary isolation.  #kittens #cats #feedingstraycats

title: Maine Coon Kittens Growing Up | Day 1 - 100!
description: This is the story of how Freya's Maine Coon kittens Antonio, Richard, Ludwig, Amadeus, Sebastian, Edvard and Clara grow up, from newborn to 100 days old! Follow them as they take their first steps, have their first taste of food, meet their relatives for the first time and learn everything else they need to know to be good cats. At the end, you will also get too see what their lives look like in their new homes!  The names in the litter are based on famous composers: * Antonio Vivaldi: Spring * Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart: Eine Kleine Nachtmusik * Ludwig van Beethoven: FÃ¼r Elise * Richard Strauss: Also Sprach Zarathustra * Clara Schumann: Piano Concerto * Edvard Grieg: Morning Mood * Johann Sebastian Bach: C Major Preulude  For more videos with my Maine Coons, take a look at my other channel:  https://www.youtube.com/@Maine_Coon_Adventures  The kittens have released their own merch collection!
